	month = may,
	year = {2023},
	keywords = {Reverse Time Migration, Data integrity, Earth, Geology, Image coding, Lossy Compression, Memory management, Performance, Performance evaluation, Seismic Imaging, Stacking},
	pages = {651--661},
	annote = {Anotações(04/03/2026, 16:09:45)
“The traditional solution transfers the vast amount of data to peripheral devices and loads them back to memory whenever needed, which may cause a substantial burden to I/O and storage space.” (Huang et al., 2023, p. 651)“In order to get the best overall RTM analysis performance, we develop a novel hybrid lossy compression method (called HyZ” (Huang et al., 2023, p. 651)“e evaluate several state-ofthe-art error-controlled lossy compression algorithms” (Huang et al., 2023, p. 651)“improves the overall performance for RTM by 6.29∼6.60× but also obtains fairly good qualities for both RTM single snapshots and the final stacking image” (Huang et al., 2023, p. 651)
},
	annote = {Só li o abstract.Esse paper fala da compressão de dados para reduzir o I/O. Ele entra na categoria de técnicas que afetam o resultado final, junto com o sistema de mudança de precisão nos dados. Este é mais adequado para o domínio da aplicação, mas vale citar os dois. 
